Overall Rating Scale
1 = serious issues with data, i.e. participant found out their parent was ill during the session, all the tasks failed, participant was asleep etc.
2 = 40-60 % of the data/session had problems
3 = A couple of small problems but overall good
4 = One small problem
5 = Don’t need to talk about it :) Session was perfect!

2020-01-28 029 AMs EDA electrodes dry so participants EDA signal was weak. Still showed sign of response to breath test but overall weak/poor signal. Eye lashes dark so eye tracking lost at some points (usually not long). Participant was sleepy during first task and lost more eye data then.
2020-01-29 043 DP EDA was strong - 15-20 - and had frequent, strong SCRs. Fine. Calibration was a little hard sometimes though. Her eye went out of frame during mushrooms, so had to put it back in.
2020-01-29 031 SP Poorly for first half, sensors are definitely dried and signals are overall not consistent. Sometimes had 2, sometimes read out 25, with really small ranges (10.002-9.998) Probably half the data was problematic\VM and DTK looked good overall, SM and Neighborhood were about 50% problematic Rough calibration to start, partially due to strange thing happening (in mushrooms) but once instructions+equipment cooperated, did just fine. tracked pupil as ellipse instead of centroid due to issues
2020-01-30 023 DP I notice that the EDA was really noisy during vanilla baseline, so I stopped the task and reapplied the sensors. It was much smoother after that. Eye went out of frame numerous times during vending machine. During the Pav phase, I had to rotate the eye-tracker, because his eye was out of frame even when at the edge of the chin rest. For Pav phase of vending machine, I accepted a calibration that was good outside of one dot that was 1.22, because we had to try several times to calibrate it and he seemed to be getting tired and agitated. I also accepted one dot at about 1.2 for the PIT phase because he had wanted to leave before then, and only agreed to do it when I told him it’d only be about 5 minutes, so I didn’t want to push my luck by continually recalibrating.
2020-01-31 042 DP EDA was a little noisier than usual, but he had very clear SCRs and the signal was generally strong (over 20). I’m a little concerned that his data somehow got mixed up with a previous participants’, because for some reason his data was named with 028 (he was 042) before I even had a chance to name it. But it was the right length (about 3 hours), and the data looks pretty smooth, so it’s probably fine. Amazingly, just fine. The only issue was that I had to recenter his eye once during vending and once during DTK.

2020-01-31 042 DP Mostly fine. He didn’t do very well, and he seemed to be ready too much into the patterns. For example, he said he spent time trying to figure out whether the side of the screen the mushroom appeared on made a difference. At first, he only pressed the button after the minion came on the screen, so I told him that the shields could be used to prevent attacks from ever occurring. A little later he figured it out. Asked me if there was a way to “leave the conversation” a ways into the instrumental phase, and I told him that he had the opportunity to interact or not interact on each trial. Asked a similar question later; seemed to have the impression that he was having continuous conversations with particular people (since the same person was presented many trials in a row), so the idea of “interacting” or “not interacting” was confusing to him.
